Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
(1:37 PM cases 22CM685, 22CF596, 22CF746, 22CF1192 called.) Defendant Joshua Cheek in court, in custody. Attorney Katherine Cook in court for Joshua Cheek. Prosecuting attorney Matthew Z Kirkpatrick in court for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant waives formal reading of the complaint and time limits for preliminary hearing in 22CF1192.
Bond is set in 22CF1192. 
Parties advise are ready to proceed with preliminary hearings in cases 22CF596, 22CF746.
State advises will proceed with case 22CF596 first.

22CF596:
State calls Sergeant Bridget Coit of the Eau Claire Police Department, who is sworn and testifies.
Attorney Cook conducts cross-examination of Sgt. Coit. 
Attorney Cook moves to admit Exhibit #1, no objection by the State. Exhibit #1 is received.
No further questions from either party, witness excused.
State makes argument for bind over and probable cause to be found.
Attorney Cook argues against bind over and advises the case should be a misdemeanor case.
Court finds probable cause and binds the case over for an Arraignment to be scheduled with Branch 5 Judicial Assistant.

22CF746:
State calls Deputy Shawn Corbin of the Eau Claire County Sheriff's Department, who is sworn and testifies.
Attorney Cook conducts cross-examination of Deputy Corbin. Witness excused.
State moves to dismiss the case. Attorney Cook has no objection.
Court orders case 22CF746 is dismissed.
Attorney Cook to schedule an Arraignment in case 22CF596 and Hearing in cases 22CF1192, 22CM685 with the Branch 5 Judicial Assistant.

Cases called at 9:30 AM: 22CF596, 22CF746. 22CM685.
Defendant Joshua Cheek in court with Attorney Katherine Cook.  Prosecuting Attorney Tiffany M. Winter in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Defendant is ordered to provide fingerprints today.
Riding with 22CF596 and 22CF746 for
Hearing scheduled for October 25, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
